cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CR

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it deals with the analysis of ad targeting on mobile devices, which involves the use of social and information networks to collect data on user behavior. It could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) because it studies how users interact with mobile ads and how they are targeted. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because it uses empirical methods to collect and analyze data on mobile ads. It could also be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) because mobile ads often involve multimedia content such as images and videos. Finally, it could be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) because it deals with the privacy implications of mobile ad targeting.
